Ok serious post now but Pendlay rows are a completely fake lift, the actual Pendlay guy who invented them intended it to be like an explosive heavy cheat row from the floor with a rounded back, basically the exact thing all meme online coaches tell you not to do no matter what

The plague of strength guy who actually was friends with Glenn Pendlay and talked to him often talked about it, apparently the guy was super mad at people misunderstanding his lift and teaching it wrong to others.

Not going to lie I think those are a bit of a meme, just doing the heavy sets with wrist wraps is enough to remove forearms and biceps from the exercise, it's very hard imo to lift heavy with reverse grip
